This file defines the main layout for the dashboard section of the application. It arranges a persistent sidebar alongside the main content area, ensuring a consistent navigation and structure for all dashboard pages.

## Purpose

The DashboardLayout component serves as a wrapper for all routes within the `/dashboard` path. It establishes a two-column structure: a left-hand sidebar for navigation and a main content area that displays the actual page content.

## Key Exports

*   **`DashboardLayout`**: A default export function component that takes `children` (React nodes) as its only prop and renders the layout.

## Props

*   **`children`**: `React.ReactNode` - The content to be rendered within the main area of the dashboard. This will typically be the specific page component for the current route.

## Usage

This component is used in `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` and is implicitly applied to all routes within the `app/dashboard` directory. For example, if you have a page at `app/dashboard/page.tsx`, its content will be rendered within the `main` element of this layout.

```typescript
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/ui/sidebar";

export default function DashboardLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-screen bg-background overflow-hidden">
      <Sidebar />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
```
